				<Text>
					<Id>1710169189754</Id>
					<Name><![CDATA[text]]></Name>
					<X>120</X><Y>200</Y>
					<Label><X>0</X><Y>-10</Y></Label>
					<PublicFlag>true</PublicFlag>
					<PresentationFlag>true</PresentationFlag>
					<ShowLabel>false</ShowLabel>
					<DrawMode>SHAPE_DRAW_2D</DrawMode>
					<EmbeddedIcon>false</EmbeddedIcon>
					<Z>0</Z>
					<Rotation>0.0</Rotation>
					<Color>-16777216</Color>
					<Text><![CDATA[The model demonstrates the mining process of an open pit coal mine from the beggining of drilling operations, 
ending with backfilling of the pit after the end of mining.

The model realizes the main processes of pit mining: drilling, backfilling, intermediate storage, 
enrichment, final storage, as well as service processes.

First, the service equipment prepares the pit for mining, gets rid of the surface layer of earth and plants. 
In the second step, drillers form holes for explosives and the blasting takes place. 
After blasting the rocks, the service vehicles clear the area and form stepped terraces 
for further work. This is how the base of the tier for the coal drilling is formed.

Once the tier is ready for drilling, the mining vehicles start extracting the minerals. 
The rocky waste is stored in a special waste landfill. The minerals are streamed 
into an intermediate storage facility. From there, they are extracted in portions and moved to one of the enrichment plants.

The objective of the beneficiation center is to recover the greatest amount of usable concentrate and separate the waste. 
The model utilizes the process of froth flotation - washing and wet separation of coal using popping 
air bubbles. First, The ore is crushed in millstones. It is then fed into a mixing chamber where the powder 
is mixed with water and reagent. In the flotation chamber following it, air is fed into the mixture. 
After flotation, three streams are obtained from the ore: useful concentrate, waste (tailings) and intermediate product, 
which has to be re-processed. At the end of the enrichment process, the useful coal concentrate is dehydrated.

At the last stage, the finished coal product is moved to the coal dump. From the dump, the coal is picked up by truck or railroad 
train. The model describes the complete cycle of coal mining until the pit is exhausted. At the end, the pit is backfilled from the waste dump.]]></Text>
					<Font>
						<Name>SansSerif</Name>
						<Size>20</Size>
						<Style>0</Style>
					</Font>
					<Alignment>LEFT</Alignment>
				</Text>
